      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Coconut trees are tall, tropical palm trees known for their slender, slightly
    curved trunks and large, feathery fronds that spread out at the top. They can
    grow up to 60\u2013100 feet tall and thrive in warm, coastal environments with
    plenty of sunlight and sandy, well-drained soil. At the crown of the tree, coconuts
    develop in clusters, each encased in a thick, fibrous husk surrounding a hard
    shell that contains the edible white flesh and refreshing coconut water inside.
    Coconut trees are highly valued for their versatility, as nearly every part of
    the tree can be used\u2014for food, oil, fiber, and building materials. They
    play an important role in tropical ecosystems and are commonly associated around
    the world."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
