  m_text: Grapes are small, round fruits that grow in clusters on woody vines, typically
    in temperate climates with plenty of sunlight. They come in a variety of colors,
    including green, red, purple, and black, each offering slightly different flavors
    ranging from sweet to mildly tart. Grapes have a smooth skin, juicy flesh, and
    may contain seeds or be seedless depending on the variety. They are rich in vitamins
    C and K, as well as antioxidants like resveratrol, which are linked to heart
    health. Grapes can be eaten fresh as a snack, dried to make raisins, or used
    in the production of juices, jams, and wine, making them a versatile and widely
    enjoyed fruit.
