  m_text: Cucumbers are refreshing, fast-growing vegetables that belong to the gourd
    family and are typically grown on trailing vines or trellises. They have a long,
    cylindrical shape with smooth or slightly bumpy green skin and a crisp, watery
    flesh inside. Known for their mild, cool flavor, cucumbers are made up of about
    95% water, making them especially hydrating and popular in salads, sandwiches,
    and beverages. They thrive in warm weather with plenty of sunlight and well-drained
    soil, and they grow quickly when properly watered. Cucumbers also provide nutrients
    like vitamin K, potassium, and antioxidants, contributing to overall health while
    adding a light, refreshing taste to a variety of dishes.
