      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Cauliflower is a cool-season vegetable known for its compact, rounded
    head\u2014called a curd\u2014made up of tightly packed, undeveloped flower buds.
    It is most commonly white, though it can also be found in green, purple, and
    orange varieties. The head is surrounded by thick green leaves that help protect
    it as it grows. Cauliflower has a mild, slightly nutty flavor and a firm texture
    that becomes soft and tender when cooked. It is rich in nutrients such as vitamin
    C, vitamin K, fiber, and antioxidants, making it a healthy addition to many diets.
    Cauliflower is highly versatile in cooking and can be roasted, steamed, mashed,
    or even used as a low-carb substitute for rice, pizza crust, or mashed potatoes."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 8f586378b4e144a9851e7b34d9b748ee, type: 2}
